+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UbCt1W61p5zV8SswAmko5u","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've thoroughly explored the codebase. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## 1. File Structure\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── .git/                          # Git repository\n├── .thunderdome/                  # Test benchmark data\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts                      # Database creation and seeding\n│   ├── models.ts                  # TypeScript interfaces\n│   ├── routes.ts                  # Express route handlers\n│   ├── server.ts                  # Express app factory\n│   ├── errors.ts                  # Error classes and handler\n│   └── seed.ts                    # Seed script\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts              # CRUD operation tests\n│   └── search.test.ts             # Search feature tests\n├── package.json                   # Dependencies and scripts\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration\n├── vitest.config.ts               # Test runner configuration\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                  # Linter configuration\n└── TASK.md                        # Project documentation\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. src/db.ts\n\nCreates and seeds a SQLite database with a notes table.\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `createDatabase(path?: string)`: Creates a SQLite database (in-memory by default), sets up WAL mode and foreign keys, creates notes table\n- `seedDatabase(db)`: Inserts 40 pre-defined notes with various topics (programming, cooking, travel, music, science, etc.)\n- `getSeedNotes()`: Returns array of 40 sample notes with titles, bodies, and JSON-stringified tags\n\n**Notes Table Schema:**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE notes (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  title TEXT NOT NULL,\n  body TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n  created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. src/models.ts\n\nTypeScript interface definitions:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. src/routes.ts\n\nExpress Router with 5 REST endpoints for notes CRUD operations:\n\n1. **GET /notes** - Lists all notes, with optional `?tag=X` query parameter for filtering\n2. **GET /notes/:id** - Gets a specific note by ID, returns 404 if not found\n3. **POST /notes** - Creates a new note (title and body required)\n   - Validates that title and body are not empty\n   - Returns 201 with the created note\n   - Tags are optional and stored as JSON string\n4. **PUT /notes/:id** - Updates an existing note\n   - Partial updates supported\n   - Updates `updated_at` timestamp\n   - Returns 404 if note doesn't exist\n5. **DELETE /notes/:id** - Deletes a note\n   - Returns 204 No Content on success\n   - Returns 404 if note doesn't exist\n\nAll routes use error handling with try-catch blocks that pass errors to next middleware.\n\n---\n\n## 5. src/server.ts\n\nCreates and exports the Express application:\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `createApp(dbPath?: string)`: Creates Express app with database, routes, and error handler\n- `createSeededApp(dbPath?: string)`: Same as above but seeds the database with sample data\n- Has a main entry point that starts the server on port 3000 if run directly\n\n**App Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n```\n\nUses middleware:\n- `express.json()` for JSON parsing\n- Custom error handler for error responses\n\n---\n\n## 6. src/errors.ts\n\nCustom error classes and Express error handler:\n\n```typescript\nexport class NotFoundError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 404;\n  constructor(message = 'Resource not found') { ... }\n}\n\nexport class ValidationError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 400;\n  constructor(message = 'Validation failed') { ... }\n}\n\nexport function errorHandler(\n  err: Error,\n  _req: Request,\n  res: Response,\n  _next: NextFunction\n): void {\n  // Returns JSON error responses with appropriate status codes\n  // 404 for NotFoundError, 400 for ValidationError\n  // 500 for all other errors\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. tests/notes.test.ts\n\n15 test cases using Vitest and Supertest for CRUD operations:\n\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag (using json_each)\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n\n---\n\n## 8. tests/search.test.ts\n\n20 comprehensive test cases for full-text search functionality:\n\n**Search Tests (1-9):**\n1. GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes\n2. Results have snippet field with highlighting\n3. Snippets contain `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n4. Results ranked by relevance (ascending rank)\n5. Exact phrase matching with quotes `\"phrase\"`\n6. Results include id, title, snippet, rank fields\n7. Non-existent searches return empty array\n8. Missing q parameter returns 400\n9. Empty q parameter returns 400\n\n**Pagination Tests (10-12):**\n10. page=1 returns first 20 results\n11. page=2 returns next results\n12. Response includes total count\n\n**Suggest Tests (13-15):**\n13. GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles\n14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n15. Empty suggest query returns 400\n\n**FTS Sync Tests (16-18):**\n16. New note appears in search immediately after creation\n17. Updated note content appears in search, old content removed\n18. Deleted note disappears from search\n\n**Robustness Tests (19-20):**\n19. Special characters in query don't crash\n20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n---\n\n## 9. package.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- **better-sqlite3**: SQLite3 database driver\n- **express**: Web framework\n- **vitest**: Fast unit test framework\n- **supertest**: HTTP assertion library for testing Express routes\n- **TypeScript**: Static typing\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` - Compile TypeScript\n- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint\n- `npm run test` - Run all tests\n- `npm run seed` - Run seed script\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **Notes App with Full-Text Search** benchmark project. It provides:\n- A REST API for managing notes (CRUD)\n- SQLite database with 40 seeded notes covering diverse topics\n- Full-text search capabilities (implied by tests, implementation in routes)\n- Comprehensive test suite with 35 total tests\n- TypeScript support with strict typing\n- Error handling and validation\n\nThe project appears to be designed for benchmarking FTS (Full-Text Search) performance in SQLite, testing both basic CRUD operations and advanced search features like snippet highlighting, relevance ranking, pagination, and prefix suggestions."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1fe850 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 30798\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 22570</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3fef43b-c020-4c3c-9d2f-941db17d8bc8","uuid":"527f9a11-4b1d-475f-980d-47b67eff3b32","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /workspace and give me a summary of:\n1. The file structure\n2. Contents of src/db.ts, src/models.ts, src/routes.ts, src/server.ts, src/errors.ts\n3. Contents of tests/notes.test.ts and tests/search.test.ts\n4. package.json for dependencies and scripts\n\nBe thorough and show me the actual file contents.","agentId":"a1fe850","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've thoroughly explored the codebase. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## 1. File Structure\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── .git/                          # Git repository\n├── .thunderdome/                  # Test benchmark data\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts                      # Database creation and seeding\n│   ├── models.ts                  # TypeScript interfaces\n│   ├── routes.ts                  # Express route handlers\n│   ├── server.ts                  # Express app factory\n│   ├── errors.ts                  # Error classes and handler\n│   └── seed.ts                    # Seed script\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts              # CRUD operation tests\n│   └── search.test.ts             # Search feature tests\n├── package.json                   # Dependencies and scripts\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript 